{"title_page": "Phil Cave", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=February 2014}}\n{{Use British English|date=February 2014}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n| name= Phil Cave\n| image = \n| caption = \n| fullname = Philip Adam Cave\n| birth_date = {{Birth date and age|1987|5|12|df=y}}\n| birth_place = [[Newcastle upon Tyne]], England\n| currentclub = [[Ashington A.F.C.|Ashington]]\n| clubnumber = \n| position = [[Defender (association football)|Defender]]\n| youthyears1 =   \n| youthclubs1 =   \n| years1 = 2003\u20132007\n| clubs1 = [[Newcastle United F.C.|Newcastle United]]\n| caps1 = 153\n| goals1 = 228\n| years2 = 2007\u20132008\n| clubs2 = [[Gateshead F.C.|Gateshead]]\n| caps2 = 41\n| goals2 = 9\n| years3 = 2008\u20132009\n| clubs3 = [[Livingston F.C.|Livingston]]\n| caps3 = 3\n| goals3 = 0\n| years4 = 2009\n| clubs4 = \u2192 [[Gateshead F.C.|Gateshead]] (loan)\n| caps4 = 17\n| goals4 = 0\n| years5 = 2009\u20132010\n| clubs5 = [[Gateshead F.C.|Gateshead]]\n| caps5 = 18\n| goals5 = 0\n| years6 = 2010\u20132012\n| clubs6 = [[Blyth Spartans A.F.C.|Blyth Spartans]]\n| caps6 = 62\n| goals6 = 3\n| years7 = 2012\u2013\n| clubs7 = [[Ashington A.F.C.|Ashington]]\n| caps7 = 0\n| goals7 = 0\n| nationalyears1 =   \n| nationalteam1 =   \n| nationalcaps1 =    \n| nationalgoals1 = \n| club-update = 10:35, 14 July 2012 (UTC)\n| ntupdate = \n}}\n'''Philip Adam Cave''' (born 12 May 1987) is an English [[association football|footballer]] who plays for [[Ashington A.F.C.|Ashington]] as a left-sided [[defender (association football)|defender]].\n\n==Career==\nCave started off as a trainee at [[Newcastle United F.C.|Newcastle United]] but did not make a first team appearance before signing for [[Gateshead F.C.|Gateshead]] in August 2007.<ref name=\"Gateshead Confirm Three New Signings\">{{cite web\n| title = Gateshead Confirm Three New Signings\n| url = http://www.gateshead-fc.com/1724/gateshead-confirm-three-new-signings\n| publisher = Gateshead F.C\n| date = 2007-08-10\n| accessdate = 2009-03-27}}</ref> Playing a pivotal role in a strong Gateshead side who won promotion via the play-offs, Cave then went on to sign for [[Livingston F.C.|Livingston]] after a successful trial.<ref name=\"Livi secure former Toon man Cave\">{{cite news\n| title = Livi secure former Toon man Cave\n| url = http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/teams/l/livingston/7531878.stm\n| publisher = BBC Sport\n| accessdate = 2009-03-27\n| date=2008-07-29}}</ref>\nAfter featuring mainly as a substitute for Livingston, Cave joined previous club Gateshead on loan until the end of the 2008\u201309 season.<ref name=\"Novak and Cave Transfer Latest\">{{cite web\n| title = Novak and Cave Transfer Latest\n| first = Jeff\n| last = Bowron\n| url = http://www.gateshead-fc.com/2164/novak-and-cave-transfer-latest\n| publisher = Gateshead F.C\n| date = 2009-02-02\n| accessdate = 2009-03-27}}</ref> Cave rejoined Gateshead for the [[2009-10 in English football|2009\u201310]] season.<ref name=\"Media Watch - 29th July\">{{cite web\n |title       = Media Watch - 29th July\n |url         = http://www.gateshead-fc.com/2339/media-watch-29th-july\n |publisher   = Gateshead F.C\n |date        = 2009-07-29\n |accessdate  = 2009-07-29\n |url-status     = dead\n |archiveurl  = https://web.archive.org/web/20120304192312/http://www.gateshead-fc.com/2339/media-watch-29th-july\n |archivedate = 4 March 2012\n |df          = dmy-all\n}}</ref> Cave was released by Gateshead at the end of the season.<ref name=\"Gateshead announce retained list\">{{cite web\n |title       = Gateshead announce retained list\n |first       = Jeff\n |last        = Bowron\n |url         = http://www.gateshead-fc.com/2769/gateshead-announce-retained-list\n |publisher   = Gateshead F.C\n |date        = 2010-05-06\n |accessdate  = 2010-05-06\n |url-status     = dead\n |archiveurl  = https://web.archive.org/web/20120830032047/http://www.gateshead-fc.com/2769/gateshead-announce-retained-list\n |archivedate = 30 August 2012\n |df          = dmy-all\n}}</ref> In July 2010 [[Conference North]] side [[Blyth Spartans A.F.C.|Blyth Spartans]] announced the signing of Cave.<ref name=\"Blyth Spartans sign Phil Cave\">{{cite web\n| title = Blyth Spartans sign Phil Cave\n| url = http://blythspartansafc.co.uk/new_php/?p=4376\n| publisher = Blyth Spartans A.F.C\n| date = 2010-07-12\n| accessdate = 2010-07-12}}</ref> After making 82 appearances in all competitions, scoring 3 goals, Cave left Blyth on 12 March 2012.<ref name=\"Phil Cave Leaves Croft Park\">{{cite web\n| title = Phil Cave Leaves Croft Park\n| url = http://blythspartansafc.co.uk/new_php/?p=8101\n| publisher = Blyth Spartans A.F.C\n| date = 2012-03-12\n| accessdate = 2012-03-15}}</ref> Cave signed for [[Ashington A.F.C.|Ashington]] on 25 May 2012.<ref name=\"Ashington sign ex-Blyth Spartans defender Phil Cave\">{{cite web\n| title = Ashington sign ex-Blyth Spartans defender Phil Cave\n| url = http://www.newspostleader.co.uk/sport/ashington-sign-ex-blyth-spartans-defender-phil-cave-1-4583204\n| publisher = News Post Leader\n| date = 2012-05-25\n| accessdate = 2012-07-14}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://blythspartansafc.co.uk/new_php/?p=4377 Phil Cave's Blyth Spartans A.F.C. profile]\n*{{soccerbase|id=52182|name=Phil Cave}}\n*{{soccerbase|id=49648|name=Phil Cave}}\n*{{Soccerway|phil-cave/34493}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Cave, Phil}}\n[[Category:1987 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Sportspeople from Newcastle upon Tyne]]\n[[Category:English footballers]]\n[[Category:Association football defenders]]\n[[Category:Newcastle United F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Gateshead F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Livingston F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Blyth Spartans A.F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Ashington A.F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Scottish Football League players]]\n[[Category:National League (English football) players]]\n[[Category:Northern Premier League players]]\n[[Category:Northern Football League players]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=February 2014}}\n{{Use British English|date=February 2014}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n| name= Phil Cave\n| image = \n| caption = \n| fullname = Philip Adam Cave\n| birth_date = {{Birth date and age|1987|5|12|df=y}}\n| birth_place = [[Newcastle upon Tyne]], England\n| currentclub = [[Ashington A.F.C.|Ashington]]\n| clubnumber = \n| position = [[Defender (association football)|Defender]]\n| youthyears1 =   \n| youthclubs1 =   \n| years1 = 2003\u20132007\n| clubs1 = [[Newcastle United F.C.|Newcastle United]]\n| caps1 = 0\n| goals1 = 0\n| years2 = 2007\u20132008\n| clubs2 = [[Gateshead F.C.|Gateshead]]\n| caps2 = 41\n| goals2 = 9\n| years3 = 2008\u20132009\n| clubs3 = [[Livingston F.C.|Livingston]]\n| caps3 = 3\n| goals3 = 0\n| years4 = 2009\n| clubs4 = \u2192 [[Gateshead F.C.|Gateshead]] (loan)\n| caps4 = 17\n| goals4 = 0\n| years5 = 2009\u20132010\n| clubs5 = [[Gateshead F.C.|Gateshead]]\n| caps5 = 18\n| goals5 = 0\n| years6 = 2010\u20132012\n| clubs6 = [[Blyth Spartans A.F.C.|Blyth Spartans]]\n| caps6 = 62\n| goals6 = 3\n| years7 = 2012\u2013\n| clubs7 = [[Ashington A.F.C.|Ashington]]\n| caps7 = 0\n| goals7 = 0\n| nationalyears1 =   \n| nationalteam1 =   \n| nationalcaps1 =    \n| nationalgoals1 = \n| club-update = 10:35, 14 July 2012 (UTC)\n| ntupdate = \n}}\n'''Philip Adam Cave''' (born 12 May 1987) is an English [[association football|footballer]] who plays for [[Ashington A.F.C.|Ashington]] as a left-sided [[defender (association football)|defender]].\n\n==Career==\nCave started off as a trainee at [[Newcastle United F.C.|Newcastle United]] but did not make a first team appearance before signing for [[Gateshead F.C.|Gateshead]] in August 2007.<ref name=\"Gateshead Confirm Three New Signings\">{{cite web\n| title = Gateshead Confirm Three New Signings\n| url = http://www.gateshead-fc.com/1724/gateshead-confirm-three-new-signings\n| publisher = Gateshead F.C\n| date = 2007-08-10\n| accessdate = 2009-03-27}}</ref> Playing a pivotal role in a strong Gateshead side who won promotion via the play-offs, Cave then went on to sign for [[Livingston F.C.|Livingston]] after a successful trial.<ref name=\"Livi secure former Toon man Cave\">{{cite news\n| title = Livi secure former Toon man Cave\n| url = http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/teams/l/livingston/7531878.stm\n| publisher = BBC Sport\n| accessdate = 2009-03-27\n| date=2008-07-29}}</ref>\nAfter featuring mainly as a substitute for Livingston, Cave joined previous club Gateshead on loan until the end of the 2008\u201309 season.<ref name=\"Novak and Cave Transfer Latest\">{{cite web\n| title = Novak and Cave Transfer Latest\n| first = Jeff\n| last = Bowron\n| url = http://www.gateshead-fc.com/2164/novak-and-cave-transfer-latest\n| publisher = Gateshead F.C\n| date = 2009-02-02\n| accessdate = 2009-03-27}}</ref> Cave rejoined Gateshead for the [[2009-10 in English football|2009\u201310]] season.<ref name=\"Media Watch - 29th July\">{{cite web\n |title       = Media Watch - 29th July\n |url         = http://www.gateshead-fc.com/2339/media-watch-29th-july\n |publisher   = Gateshead F.C\n |date        = 2009-07-29\n |accessdate  = 2009-07-29\n |url-status     = dead\n |archiveurl  = https://web.archive.org/web/20120304192312/http://www.gateshead-fc.com/2339/media-watch-29th-july\n |archivedate = 4 March 2012\n |df          = dmy-all\n}}</ref> Cave was released by Gateshead at the end of the season.<ref name=\"Gateshead announce retained list\">{{cite web\n |title       = Gateshead announce retained list\n |first       = Jeff\n |last        = Bowron\n |url         = http://www.gateshead-fc.com/2769/gateshead-announce-retained-list\n |publisher   = Gateshead F.C\n |date        = 2010-05-06\n |accessdate  = 2010-05-06\n |url-status     = dead\n |archiveurl  = https://web.archive.org/web/20120830032047/http://www.gateshead-fc.com/2769/gateshead-announce-retained-list\n |archivedate = 30 August 2012\n |df          = dmy-all\n}}</ref> In July 2010 [[Conference North]] side [[Blyth Spartans A.F.C.|Blyth Spartans]] announced the signing of Cave.<ref name=\"Blyth Spartans sign Phil Cave\">{{cite web\n| title = Blyth Spartans sign Phil Cave\n| url = http://blythspartansafc.co.uk/new_php/?p=4376\n| publisher = Blyth Spartans A.F.C\n| date = 2010-07-12\n| accessdate = 2010-07-12}}</ref> After making 82 appearances in all competitions, scoring 3 goals, Cave left Blyth on 12 March 2012.<ref name=\"Phil Cave Leaves Croft Park\">{{cite web\n| title = Phil Cave Leaves Croft Park\n| url = http://blythspartansafc.co.uk/new_php/?p=8101\n| publisher = Blyth Spartans A.F.C\n| date = 2012-03-12\n| accessdate = 2012-03-15}}</ref> Cave signed for [[Ashington A.F.C.|Ashington]] on 25 May 2012.<ref name=\"Ashington sign ex-Blyth Spartans defender Phil Cave\">{{cite web\n| title = Ashington sign ex-Blyth Spartans defender Phil Cave\n| url = http://www.newspostleader.co.uk/sport/ashington-sign-ex-blyth-spartans-defender-phil-cave-1-4583204\n| publisher = News Post Leader\n| date = 2012-05-25\n| accessdate = 2012-07-14}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://blythspartansafc.co.uk/new_php/?p=4377 Phil Cave's Blyth Spartans A.F.C. profile]\n*{{soccerbase|id=52182|name=Phil Cave}}\n*{{soccerbase|id=49648|name=Phil Cave}}\n*{{Soccerway|phil-cave/34493}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Cave, Phil}}\n[[Category:1987 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Sportspeople from Newcastle upon Tyne]]\n[[Category:English footballers]]\n[[Category:Association football defenders]]\n[[Category:Newcastle United F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Gateshead F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Livingston F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Blyth Spartans A.F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Ashington A.F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Scottish Football League players]]\n[[Category:National League (English football) players]]\n[[Category:Northern Premier League players]]\n[[Category:Northern Football League players]]\n", "name_user": "82.38.237.14", "label": "unsafe", "comment